{
  "texts": [
    "The various intelligent approaches are customized to ensure robust swing-up control of the SLRIP and to dynamically adapt the strategies to dynamic changes in the environment such as external disturbances and unstructured dynamic variations.",
    "• The developed RL algorithms hold a huge potential to contribute to the design and implementation of real-time controllers for automation and mechatronic systems aiming for optimized performances.",
    "• The proposed research strategy will advance the state-of-the-art knowledge in RL with a focus on intelligent control applications.",
    "Further, this type of research can be employed by a broad range of other robotic systems.In this paper, the swing-up and stabilization control of a SLRIP is developed by training and testing RL algorithms.",
    "The developed RL control methods are compared with the PID and LQR swing-up control."
  ]
}